The 37-year-old concluded his journey with 7,195 runs in 103 Tests and an impressive 21,301 first-class runs. He expressed gratitude to the BCCI, teammates, family, and fans for their unwavering support throughout his career.
title: Pujara retirement: What is written on his goodbye post? Read inside

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: In Greater Noida, a six-year-old witnessed his mother's horrific murder by his father and grandparents, who doused her in liquid, slapped her, and set her ablaze due to dowry demands. Nikki succumbed to her injuries in a Delhi hospital. Her husband has been arrested, while the other family members are on the run, facing charges of murder and conspiracy.
title: 'Slapped my mother, set her on fire': Son’s shocking account in Greater Noida ‘dowry’ death; husband held

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Tom Brady celebrated his son Jack's 18th birthday. He shared photos and heartfelt messages. Gisele Bundchen, Brady's ex-wife, did not post a public message. She shared photos of her younger children. This difference sparked online discussion. It highlights how blended families manage milestones. Social media silence doesn't always indicate a problem. It can be a choice to protect privacy.
title: Gisele Bündchen vs Jack Brady: Accused of ‘erasing’ Tom's son; shifts focus to new family

author: TNN
description: Following the tragic stabbing death of Nayan Santani at a school in Maninagar, his father, Girish Santani, expressed his grief and demanded the harshest punishment for the perpetrators during a condolence meet. He criticized the school's negligence and called for its closure, while political figures assured strict action and emphasized maintaining law and order.

description: Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg is betting big on small, elite AI teams, like the secretive TBD Lab led by Alexandr Wang, to develop advanced AI models. This shift towards smaller, agile groups mirrors a Silicon Valley trend, but has sparked internal tensions at Meta.

description: Apple has sued a former Apple Watch engineer, Dr. Chen Shi, Oppo, and InnoPeak Technology, alleging trade secret theft related to health sensor technology. Oppo denies involvement but pledges to cooperate with the legal process, while Apple cites suspicious digital activity by Shi.

description: Australian fast bowler Lance Morris is set to miss the Ashes series and will be sidelined for 12 months following back surgery. The 27-year-old, who was a potential backup pace option, withdrew from the South Africa one-day series due to lower back discomfort. Tests revealed a lumbar bone stress injury, prompting the surgery.

description: A significant 7.4 magnitude earthquake rattled the Drake Passage on August 22, 2025, triggering tsunami warnings for Antarctic bases. While a widespread tsunami was averted, the event underscores the region's seismic activity and its crucial role in global climate regulation. The passage, notorious for extreme weather and treacherous navigation, is vital for ocean currents and carbon absorption.
title: Drake passage 2025 earthquake: 7.4-magnitude tremor; world’s most dangerous waters

description: The Defence Research and Development Organisation (DRDO) successfully conducted maiden flight tests of the Integrated Air Defence Weapon System (IADWS) off the Odisha coast on August 23, 2025. This multi-layered air defence platform integrates indigenous components like QRSAM, VSHORADS, and a Directed Energy Weapon.
title: India successfully tests maiden flight of Integrated Air Defence Weapon system; watch

description: LeBron James' foray into golf during the 2025 NBA offseason became a viral sensation, not for his prowess, but for his notably stiff swing. NFL and NBA stars humorously critiqued his form, while fans created memes. Undeterred, James embraced the challenge, vowing to improve and showcasing a relatable side of the basketball icon.

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: The newly unveiled MCA Sharad Pawar Cricket Museum at Wankhede Stadium, while lauded for its design and exhibits, has stirred debate over its naming. Viren Rasquinha's comment sparked discussion about honoring administrators versus players. The museum celebrates Mumbai's cricketing history, featuring interactive displays and memorabilia, opening to the public on September 22, 2025.

description: Rahul Gandhi and Tejashwi Yadav rode motorbikes during their "Vote Adhikaar Yatra" in Bihar, aiming to address concerns about voter roll irregularities. The Yatra, spanning over 1,300 kilometres, seeks to mobilize people against alleged manipulation in the electoral roll revision process, which the opposition claims targets poor, minorities, and migrant workers, leading to vote theft.

author: SHIVA KUMAR PINNA
description: In Jayashankar Bhupalpally, a teacher allegedly poisoned drinking water with pesticide, targeting rival teachers. Eleven students fell ill after consuming the contaminated water and were hospitalized. The accused, Rajender, aimed to frame Venu and Suryaprakash amidst school dominance struggles, leading to his suspension along with the other two teachers and the cook.

description: Tom Brady celebrated his son Jack's 18th birthday with an emotional tribute, highlighting Jack's admirable qualities. Chopra asserts that Shubman Gill is the likely successor to Rohit Sharma, already holding vice-captaincy in ODIs and leading in Tests. Gill's rise has also shifted Axar Patel from T20 vice-captaincy, solidifying Gill's position as the heir apparent for India's white-ball leadership.
